---
/**
 * consensus-deep-dive · Figure 2 — the three configuration valences
 * (0-valent / 1-valent / bivalent).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/distributed-systems/consensus-deep-dive.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). Isolated as an .astro component because MDX's JSX
 * parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes. This
 * figure references no shared arrowhead markers, so it carries no <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 150"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Three configuration valences: 0-valent sealed on 0, 1-valent sealed on 1, bivalent both still reachable"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <rect x="14" y="40" width="160" height="84" rx="10" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
            <text x="94" y="64" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >0-valent</text
            >
            <text x="94" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >every run from here</text
            >
            <text x="94" y="98" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >decides 0 — sealed,</text
            >
            <text x="94" y="112" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >even if nobody knows</text
            >
            <rect x="200" y="40" width="160" height="84" rx="10" fill="#fff" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="280"
                y="64"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">1-valent</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >symmetrically</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="98" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >sealed on 1</text
            >
            <rect
                x="386"
                y="40"
                width="160"
                height="84"
                rx="10"
                fill="#f1eee2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="466"
                y="64"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">bivalent</text
            >
            <text x="466" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >both 0 and 1 still</text
            >
            <text x="466" y="98" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >reachable — the</text
            >
            <text x="466" y="112" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >future is undecided</text
            >
            <text
                x="280"
                y="22"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110"
                >"univalent" = the outcome is already fixed; "bivalent" = it isn't</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The proof is two lemmas: a bivalent <em>start</em> exists, and from any bivalent config the adversary
        can <em>stay</em> bivalent forever.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
